During a meeting with top executives of health insurance companies, President Trump announced that the companies have agreed to waive all copays on coronavirus testing and extend coverage for coronavirus treatment in all of their benefit plans. They have also agreed to cover telemedicine and eliminate surprise billing. The President praised the collaboration and partnership between the government and the insurance companies in addressing the coronavirus outbreak. The President also mentioned that the government is working closely with the cruise line and airline industries to implement measures to prevent the spread of the virus. Additionally, he mentioned successful collaborations with the state of California, Canada, and the UK in dealing with the outbreak. Various executives from the insurance companies and a governor expressed their support for the efforts to ensure access to testing and treatment for all Americans. The President confirmed that he will be going to Capitol Hill later in the day.